                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 12, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>389. Your 738, October 10, 6 p.m. Instruct Mukden promptly to inform the
                    Department of any new developments bearing upon the statement of the Japanese
                    Consulate General reported in last sentence of Mukden’s telegram of October 10,
                    11 a.m. to the Legation, or upon any other phase of the question, and to take no
                    new steps in relation to this matter without first informing the Department and
                    requesting instructions; also to transmit a full report by mail despatch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
